1 unit Lemon
1 unit Baby Lettuce
1 unit Chickpeas
2 ounce Prosciutto
1.5 ounce Honey Dijon Dressing
1 teaspoon Chili Flakes
6 tablespoon Parmesan Cheese
½ ounce Sunflower Seeds
1 unit Croutons
Salt
Pepper

• Wash and dry produce.

• Halve lemon. Trim and discard root end from lettuce; roughly chop into
bite-size pieces. Drain and rinse chickpeas; thoroughly pat dry with
paper towels. Roughly tear prosciutto into bite-size pieces.

• In a large bowl, whisk together honey Dijon dressing, juice from half
the lemon (whole lemon for 4 servings), a pinch of salt and pepper, and
as many chili flakes as you like.

• To bowl with dressing mixture, add lettuce, chickpeas, Parmesan, and
sunflower seeds; toss to combine.

• Divide salad between bowls. Top with prosciutto and croutons. Serve.